# vLLM 0.19.1-t5 recipe for DGX Spark (ARM64 + Blackwell SM_120)
#
# Built ON TOP OF scitrera/cuda-containers's pre-existing recipe pipeline
# (Dockerfile.llm_inference + build-image.sh). See:
#   - dgx-spark-vllm/RECIPE-NOTES.md   for the pin matrix and bump rationale
#   - dgx-spark-vllm/README.md         for build invocation
#   - dgx-spark-vllm/build.sh          for the wrapper that calls upstream
#
# Goal: NVFP4 quantization support (e.g. sakamakismile/Qwen3.6-27B-NVFP4
# and the Text-NVFP4-MTP sibling). Per the model cards: NVFP4 + Blackwell
# SM_120 needs vLLM >= 0.19, tested on 0.19.1rc1.
#
# Delta vs scitrera's published vllm-0.17.0-t5.recipe (4 lines, see
# RECIPE-NOTES.md "Recipe diff vs 0.17.0-t5" for the rationale):
#   - VLLM_VERSION         0.17.0  -> 0.19.1
#   - FLASHINFER_VERSION   0.6.5   -> 0.6.6  (vLLM 0.19.1 cuda.txt pin)
#   - TRANSFORMERS_VERSION 5.3.0   -> 5.5.3  (vLLM 0.19.1 excludes 5.0-5.5.0;
#                                             5.5.3 matches scitrera's
#                                             sglang-0.5.10 known-good)
#   - IMAGE_TAG            scitrera/...:0.17.0-t5 -> local/...:0.19.1-t5-dev
#                          (local/ namespace so it cannot shadow upstream)
#
# Everything else (DEV_BASE_IMAGE, RUN_BASE_IMAGE, TRITON_VERSION, CUDA via
# the -v2-cu131 base) stays IDENTICAL to scitrera's prod 0.17.0-t5 — that
# is the whole point of choosing 0.19.1 over 0.20.0 (which would require
# the 2.11.0-v1-cu132 base).

DOCKERFILE=Dockerfile.llm_inference
TARGET=vllm_runtime

DEV_BASE_IMAGE=scitrera/dgx-spark-pytorch-dev:2.10.0-v2-cu131
RUN_BASE_IMAGE=scitrera/dgx-spark-pytorch-runtime:2.10.0-v2-cu131

FLASHINFER_VERSION=0.6.6
TRITON_VERSION=3.6.0

TRANSFORMERS_VERSION=5.5.3
#TRANSFORMERS_REF=""

VLLM_VERSION=0.19.1

IMAGE_TAG=local/dgx-spark-vllm:0.19.1-t5-dev
